# ngjs-hello-world (Benchmark 1)

Tiny AngularJS 1.x app used as a sanity-check benchmark for EVUA.

## Covers
- Module detection
- Controller detection
- ng-controller wiring
- Basic template interpolation ({{ message }})
- Snapshot-based semantic validation
- Zero-risk migration baseline

## Expected Migration Risks
- Very low risk
- No watchers
- No services
- No async
- No routing

## Validation
- Jasmine unit test for controller state
- JSON before/after snapshots to validate semantic equivalence post-migration

## Failure Means
If this fails, the migration pipeline is fundamentally broken.
